  "market_context": "On the ES hourly chart, price reached down into a fair value gap and formed a closure back inside the previous candle range, leaving a large lower wick. This setup signaled potential bullish continuation if the upper half of the wick was respected.",
  "key_observation": "When price closes back inside the previous candle range after reaching a fair value gap and leaves a large wick, the 0.5 of that wick should be respected on the lower time frame for expansion in the anticipated direction.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify on the hourly chart that price has reached into a fair value gap and closed back inside the previous candle range, forming a large wick.",
    "Step 2: Anticipate bullish expansion since the wick suggests rejection from the discount fair value gap.",
    "Step 3: Mark the 0.5 level of the hourly wick as the threshold that must be respected for the bullish scenario to remain valid.",
    "Step 4: Drop down to the 5-minute chart to look for an open-low-high-close delivery sequence that respects 50% of the hourly wick.",
    "Step 5: Confirm price opens, forms its low within the fair value gap (above 50% of the wick), and then expands higher out of the upper half of the wick."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price formed its low within the fair value gap, respected 50% of the hourly wick, and expanded higher out of the upper half of the wick as anticipated.",
  "lessons": "After a fair value gap reaches and closes back inside with a large wick, use 0.5 of that wick as the protective threshold on the lower time frame; an open-low-high-close sequence above that level confirms continuation.",
